rComments: The homeworks are fairly easy, but be careful for the strict grading. Tests are fair, but they ask a lot of questions over the smallest details covered in class. There is a mandatory all-day "volunteer" trip, which is kind of stupid and a waste of my Saturday. Just try to memorize as much as possible for tests, and go to office hours for HW answers
Horrible teacher. Has another helper who teaches the way he likes. You become more confused after attending the class.

Classes are interesting and fun to attend. The railroad engineers are an excellent group of students. Exams are formatted weird but not too bad. If you are interested in railroads, this is the guy to talk to fuel your knowledge in terms of job placement, research, and experience.
